The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Videocon Industries has empowered its board to raise Rs 1,500 crore under qualified institutional placement guidelines. The EGM adopted a special resolution to this effect, the company informed the stock exchanges. The EGM authorised the board of directors to issue, offer and allot equity shares or securities other than warrants for an amount not exceeding Rs 1,500 crore, it said. 

 Tata Indicom and Mast Mobile Media have joined hands for mobile advertising solutions on the Tata Indicom network. Mast Mobile Media will provide Tata Indicom with ad-serving technology for its Brew and WAP data services, using Mast Mobiles advertising engine.

 Vijaya Bank has inaugurated a branch at Garia and another at the East Calcutta Township Project Area. The bank plans to open eight more branches in the eastern region, including four in Bengal. Two of them will be in Calcutta. The bank plans to have 1,000 branches by the end of this fiscal.

 Aptech Ltd has officially opened its maiden office in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. The company has also announced the inauguration of a training centre at Antarabangsa. The company plans to offer services and solutions to individuals, companies and academic institutions in the country.

 Vestas Wind Systems subsidiary, NEG Micon India, will henceforth be known as Vestas Wind Technology India Pvt Ltd. This is a move to reposition the companys operations in India, which in 2005 was the groups third biggest market after the US and Germany.

 Shree Pacetronix Ltd (Pacetronix) will be launching a pacemaker with a 20-year life. The company and the state government have launched a BPL pacemaker for the under-privileged patients, which is available for Rs 20,000.

 Oriental Containers Ltd, the packaging arm of Oricon Enterprises Ltd, has entered into a licensing agreement with US-based Silgan White Cap for transfer of technology to manufacture twist-off closures at its plant near Mumbai.

 Tanla Solutions public offer, which was launched on December 11, has been oversubscribed 39 times. The qualified institutional buyer (QIB) portion was oversubscribed 57 times, the high net worth individual (HNI) portion 41.56 times and the retail portion 11.1 times.

 Bank of India (BoI) has launched a business delivery model, Retail Hub, at its Salt Lake branch premises. The model is based on assembly line concept to offer customised retail credit facilities.

